translated: Ebert, Evan, practicing physician, Gothenburg, b. 6/10/94 in Helsingborg. Married in 1931 to Elsa André. — Graduated from high school in Helsingborg in 1913, medical candidate in Stockholm in 1918 and medical licentiate there in 1923. Studied in Copenhagen, Paris, and USA. Extraordinary assistant and assistant in anatomy in Lund in 1917 and 1922-23. Short-term medical appointments as substitute doctor at Vänersborg hospital in 1919 and as provisional doctor in Gäddede, Eringsboda, and Skönneruds district in 1921, in Bergsjö district in 1923 and 1924, as a university doctor at Svienshögen's Sanatorium in 1922 and Saltsjöbadens Bathhouse in 1923-24, assistant doctor at Sabbatsberg Hospital surgical ward in 1923-24, and at Örebro hospital in the same year, sub-acting doctor at Örebro hospital surgical department on various occasions in 1924, 1925, and 1927, at Alingsås hospital in 1925, assistant doctor at Seraf Hospital ear clinic in 1925-26, extraordinary assistant at the Academy Hospital ear clinic in 1926-27, resident doctor at Sahlgren Hospital ear department in 1927-28, and assistant doctor there in 1928-29, various consultant doctor appointments in the ear department, practicing physician in Gothenburg with a specialization in ear, nose, and throat diseases since 1929. Published articles in professional journals.
